args: Princess, please. You need to stay inside\nuntil your fever passes.
I know, I just... I'm supposed to be out\nthere healing the sick, and yet here I am,\nsick myself.
It was inevitable, considering how\nhard you've been workingâ€”and with\nso little rest.
Wait here. I'll bring you some food.
...You want me to make food for Zethia?\nI... I need to think on that.
Oh, I'm sorry, young man.\nI think I'll have to pass.
The rift between Zethia and her people\nis as wide as ever...
Perhaps I should just do it myself...?\nNo, I'm no cook. I'd probably end up\nkilling her.
Hm? Oh, you're the pair I always see\nplaying in the courtyard. Is something\nthe matter?

We got hungry, so we came to see if we
could get some food. There's waaaay
more food around now that we've got
the Shepherds protecting us!
I heard it's 'cause the fiends are scared\nnow, so they don't come near our fields!\nHey, are there any strawberries left?
Yes, but... Would you mind if I saved them\nfor Princess Zethia? She's not feeling well,\nand I can't cook.
I'd thought strawberries might be a good\nsolution.
Wait, you can't cook?!\nBut you're so muscly and cool!
Heh, unfortunately there's more to cooking\nthan that.
Weird. Well, we can help you, Mister\nChrom! Our mom's had us helping\nin the kitchen since we could walk.
Really? That's very kind of you.
We wanna thank Miss Zethia for healing\neveryone, too! We're not super chefs or\nanything, but we'll do our best!
Ha ha, thank you.\nShall we get started, then?
I thought we had it in the bag when you\nstarted choppin' those veggies in the air,\nbut...
Guess we shoulda just kept it simple.
We can't ask her to eat this...\nWe have to do something.
THERE you two are! How many times have\nI told you not to go wanderingâ€” Hold on,\nwhat's going on here?
Mom! You're just in time. We were trying\nto cook something for Miss Zethia, but\nwe messed it up!
Oh, I'm sure it can't be that bad... Wait,\ndid you just say it was for Zethia?
Yeah! She got sick 'cause she was helping\neveryone out all the time, so we wanted to\ndo something nice to help her feel better.
And now that you're here, we're gonna\nknock it outta the park! Good thing, too,\n'cause Mister Chrom is NOT a good cook...
For Zethia...\nNo... No, I can't possibly...
What's wrong? Miss Zethia always helps\nus. She helps everybody!
Why can't we help her now?
I wanna help! I LOVE helping!
...You're right. I'll do my part as well.\nGoodness, I wish you two were this\nexcited to help ME in the kitchen...
Are you sure you don't mind? I know\nmany of you still harbor animosity for\nthe princess.
That's true, but my children have helped\nme open my eyes.
Deep down, I think we all knew Zethia fell\nill because she was overworking herself\nfor our sakes.
We should be doing what we can to\nease her burden, not shunning her.\nRight, ladies?
Well, I guess I WOULD feel a bit guilty\nsitting out now.
The princess deserves our gratitude.\nI'm happy to do my part in that.
Well, you have my thanks. And I'm\nsure Princess Zethia will be quite\nmoved as well.
Now, we have some cooking to do!\nEveryone, er...to arms!
Is that you, Chrom? Please, come in.
Oh! Wh-what are you two doing here?
Do you still have a fever? Well don't worry,\nall of us worked together to make you\nsomething to help you feel better!
You're always helping everybody out,\nso this is our way of saying ï¼‚thanks\na whole bunch!ï¼‚
That's very nice of you, but... What do you\nmean by ï¼‚all of usï¼‚?
She means everyone in the Halidom.\nBelieve it or not, they've all been\nworried about you.
Regardless of what you might have been\nbefore, you're their friend now.
If you don't believe me, just take a bite.\nFood this good is beyond me, I assure you.
Holy molyâ€”it's so good she's\nactually crying!
Ha ha... You have no idea how happy\nthis makes me.
Hee hee! Yay! I'm gonna go tell everyone!
Gods, I wish I had that kind of energy...
I didn't expect to be moved to tears...\nForgive me. You must think me weak.

Nonsense. My younger sister cries more
than most, but she's among the strongest
people I know. I think it's a waste to stifle
your emotions, especially the good ones.
Heh... Your sister sounds lovely. I would\nbe honored to meet her someday.
Perhaps you might, so long as hope\ncontinues to bloom in this world.
Maybe so. At the very least, this meal\nhas made me believe the future I long\nfor may not be completely out of reach.
I know this gesture doesn't mean I'm\nforgiven for everything I did as the\nEmpress.
But I want to think it means that my efforts\nsince then have reached them in some\nsmall way.
That it wasn't all for nothing...
Of course it wasn't. Everything you've done\nâ€”everything we're DOINGâ€”it's all making\na future of hope.
Each step along the way helps us better\nunderstand and support each other going\nforward.
So let's keep going, Zethia.\nAll of us, together. Let's keep fighting\nfor the future you deserve.
